.TH FUSE-OVERLAYFS 1 "2026-05-06" "fuse-overlayfs 1.16" "InterGenOS User Manual"
.SH NAME
fuse-overlayfs \- overlay filesystem in userspace
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fuse-overlayfs
[\fB\-o\fP \fIoptions\fP] \fImountpoint\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBfuse-overlayfs\fP provides an overlay filesystem implemented as a
FUSE (Filesystem in Userspace) mount. It allows stacking writable
upper layers over read-only lower layers, the same semantic as the
in-kernel overlayfs, but without requiring kernel support or root
privileges.
.PP
This is the primary storage driver for rootless Podman containers
on hosts that do not support user-namespace overlay mounts. It
provides full POSIX semantics including whiteouts, opaque
directories, and extended attributes for storage layers.
.SH OPTIONS
Options are passed via the \fB\-o\fP flag as a comma-separated list:
.TP
.B lowerdir=\fIdir\fP
Read-only lower layer.
.TP
.B upperdir=\fIdir\fP
Writable upper layer.
.TP
.B workdir=\fIdir\fP
Working directory (must be on the same filesystem as upperdir).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR podman (1),
.BR fuse (8),
.BR mount.fuse (8)
.PP
Upstream documentation:
.UR https://github.com/containers/fuse-overlayfs
.UE .
